7d90c6d40751cd8d6411d23b3dc0b6b8b2b347ca
2026-05-21
feat: HomeComponent scroll exit + single-page integration (#25)

HomeComponent now composes HeroSectionComponent + ResumeSectionComponent in
normal document flow. Scroll-driven hero exit animation via exitProgress
computed signal (0 → 1 as scrollY advances through window.innerHeight).

exitProgress formula: clamp(scrollY / innerHeight, 0, 1)
- Desktop: opacity = 1 - exitProgress, transform = translateY(-p * 60px)
- isLowPerf: opacity only, no transform
- SSR: isPlatformBrowser guard — exitProgress stays 0, no window access

heroOpacity and heroTransform are computed signals bound via [style.opacity]
and [style.transform] on a .hero-container wrapper. will-change set on the
container for compositor promotion.

Router changes:
- Remove /resume route (per ADR-0001; ResumeComponent deleted)
- Add withInMemoryScrolling({ anchorScrolling: enabled, scrollPositionRestoration: enabled })
  so /#about fragment navigation works from any starting route

Ships 8 specs: HeroSection in DOM, ResumeSection in DOM, exitProgress=0 at
scrollY=0, exitProgress=1 at scrollY=innerHeight, exitProgress clamped to 1
when overscrolled, heroTransform=null on isLowPerf, heroTransform contains
translateY on desktop, exitProgress=0 on server platform.

Files changed:
  src/app/pages/home/home.ts
  src/app/pages/home/home.html
  src/app/pages/home/home.scss
  src/app/pages/home/home.spec.ts (new)
  src/app/app.routes.ts
  src/app/app.config.ts
  src/app/pages/resume/resume.ts (deleted)
  src/app/pages/resume/resume.html (deleted)
  src/app/pages/resume/resume.scss (deleted)

Closes #25.
